The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Yamaha hives off sales arm

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Sept. 29: Yamaha Motor India today hived off its sales and marketing division to form Yamaha Motor India Sales (P) Limited.

 The new entity will be a wholly-owned subsidiary of Yamaha Motor Company, Japan and will focus on domestic sales, marketing and after-sales services. 

 The new company shows Yamahas corporate strategy for India, which is seen as a major market and manufacturing centre, the company said. The new entity will kick-start its operations from next month and will have T. Maeda as its director. He will be assisted by Atul Gupta, head-sales and marketing. 




